ta-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Quinto · Pompeio · Sosio\n                    Clementiano\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Quinto\">Q(uinto)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Pompeio\">Pompeio\u003C/span> · Sosio \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Clementiano\">Cl\u003Cspan class=\"apex\" title=\"apex over: e\">é\u003C/span>mentiano\u003C/span>\u003C/span> · \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>filio · et infanti \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>dulcissimo · qui vixit \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>mensib(us) · VII · dieb(us) · X\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">X͡V\u003C/span>III \u003Cbr id=\"al7-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>parentes \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>DMS\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Quinto · Pompeio · Sosio\n                    Clementiano\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Quinto\">Q\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Pompeio\">POMPEIO\u003C/span>·SOSIO\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Clementiano\">CL\u003Cspan class=\"apex\" title=\"apex over: e\">é\u003C/span>MENTIANO\u003C/span>\u003C/span>·\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>FILIO·ETINFANTI\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>DULCISSIMO·QUIVIXIT\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>MENSIB·VII·DIEB·X\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">X͡V\u003C/span>III\u003Cbr id=\"al7-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>PARENTES\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003150_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\" src=\"ISic003150_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003150.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\" src=\"ISic003150-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003150_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\" src=\"ISic003150_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003150_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\" src=\"ISic003150_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of Prag from photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"4\">4: \u003Cspan>The F of infanti has a substantial foot, giving the appearance of an E (visual confusion between these letters not uncommon in C2-C3 inscriptions); the A of infanti lacks a cross-bar.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Sacred to the spirits of the underworld. To Quintus Pompeius Sosius Clementianus, son and sweetest newborn, who lived for 7 months and 28 days, erected by his parents\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Given that Biscari undertook excavations at Centuripe, and that the family of the Pompeii Sosii has part of its origin in Centuripe, it is at least as possible that the stone comes originally from Centuripe as from Catania. It seems most likely that Clementianus is the son of a freedman of the family.\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Korhonen's suggestion that the apices/interpuncts in line 6 serve to indicate abbreviations cannot stand given that the sign appears after the numeral VII also, so they serve simply to separate all elements on the line, as is typical.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Mommsen 1883 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buch/4004\" target=\"_blank\">1088*.282\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001137\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001137\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Huelsen 1894 24510 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000268\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000268\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 13 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>V-cut letters of slightly irregular module and height, with pronounced serifs. Interpuncts are above the line and not clearly distinguishable from apices\u003C/p> Line 1-7  17-21  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[234,237,240,243,246,249,252,255],{"id":235,"html":236},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>D(is) m(anibus) s(acrum) \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Quinto · Pompeio · Sosio\n                    Clementiano\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Quinto\">Q(uinto)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Pompeio\">Pompeio\u003C/span> · Sosio \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Clementiano\">Cl\u003Cspan class=\"apex\" title=\"apex over: e\">é\u003C/span>mentiano\u003C/span>\u003C/span> · \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>filio · et infanti \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>dulcissimo · qui vixit \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>mensib(us) · VII · dieb(us) · X\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">X͡V\u003C/span>III \u003Cbr id=\"al7-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>parentes \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>DMS\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Quinto · Pompeio · Sosio\n                    Clementiano\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Quinto\">Q\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Pompeio\">POMPEIO\u003C/span>·SOSIO\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Clementiano\">CL\u003Cspan class=\"apex\" title=\"apex over: e\">é\u003C/span>MENTIANO\u003C/span>\u003C/span>·\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>FILIO·ETINFANTI\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>DULCISSIMO·QUIVIXIT\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>MENSIB·VII·DIEB·X\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">X͡V\u003C/span>III\u003Cbr id=\"al7-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>PARENTES\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":238,"html":239},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003150_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\" src=\"ISic003150_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003150.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\" src=\"ISic003150-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003150_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\" src=\"ISic003150_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003150_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\" src=\"ISic003150_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":241,"html":242},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of Prag from photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"4\">4: \u003Cspan>The F of infanti has a substantial foot, giving the appearance of an E (visual confusion between these letters not uncommon in C2-C3 inscriptions); the A of infanti lacks a cross-bar.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":244,"html":245},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Sacred to the spirits of the underworld. To Quintus Pompeius Sosius Clementianus, son and sweetest newborn, who lived for 7 months and 28 days, erected by his parents\u003C/p>  ",{"id":247,"html":248},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Given that Biscari undertook excavations at Centuripe, and that the family of the Pompeii Sosii has part of its origin in Centuripe, it is at least as possible that the stone comes originally from Centuripe as from Catania. It seems most likely that Clementianus is the son of a freedman of the family.\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Korhonen's suggestion that the apices/interpuncts in line 6 serve to indicate abbreviations cannot stand given that the sign appears after the numeral VII also, so they serve simply to separate all elements on the line, as is typical.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":250,"html":251},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Mommsen 1883 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buch/4004\" target=\"_blank\">1088*.282\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001137\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001137\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Huelsen 1894 24510 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000268\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000268\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 13 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":253,"html":254},"handnote","\u003Cp>V-cut letters of slightly irregular module and height, with pronounced serifs. Interpuncts are above the line and not clearly distinguishable from apices\u003C/p> Line 1-7  17-21  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":256,"html":257},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[259,261,264,265],{"html":260},"Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP",{"id":262,"lang":141,"html":263},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>D(is) m(anibus) s(acrum) \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Quinto · Pompeio · Sosio\n                    Clementiano\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Quinto\">Q(uinto)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Pompeio\">Pompeio\u003C/span> · Sosio \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Clementiano\">Cl\u003Cspan class=\"apex\" title=\"apex over: e\">é\u003C/span>mentiano\u003C/span>\u003C/span> · \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>filio · et infanti \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>dulcissimo · qui vixit \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>mensib(us) · VII · dieb(us) · X\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">X͡V\u003C/span>III \u003Cbr id=\"al7-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>parentes \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":260},{"id":266,"lang":141,"html":267},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>DMS\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Quinto · Pompeio · Sosio\n                    Clementiano\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Quinto\">Q\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Pompeio\">POMPEIO\u003C/span>·SOSIO\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Clementiano\">CL\u003Cspan class=\"apex\" title=\"apex over: e\">é\u003C/span>MENTIANO\u003C/span>\u003C/span>·\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>FILIO·ETINFANTI\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>DULCISSIMO·QUIVIXIT\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>MENSIB·VII·DIEB·X\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">X͡V\u003C/span>III\u003Cbr id=\"al7-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>PARENTES\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[269,271,274,276],{"image":114,"thumb":270,"title":117},"ISic003150_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":272,"thumb":273,"title":117},"ISic003150.jpg","ISic003150-thumb.jpg",{"image":120,"thumb":275,"title":117},"ISic003150_rear_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":277,"thumb":278,"title":117},"ISic003150_rear.jpg","ISic003150_rear-thumb.jpg",[280],{"html":66},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Epitaph of Quintus Pompeius Sosius Clementianus\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JCu\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728\">James Cummings\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>conversion to EpiDoc\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"AA\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>EpiDoc editing and English translation\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n\t    \u003CrespStmt>\n     \t       \u003Cname xml:id=\"SS\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569\">Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n     \t       \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n \t   \u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003CrespStmt>\u003Cname xml:id=\"Coccato\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6641-2820\">Alessia Coccato\u003C/name>\u003Cresp>Petrographic observation and analysis\u003C/resp>\u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic003150\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\">285099\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\">13800758\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003150\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-18\">10.5281/zenodo.4357188\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Catania\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/018\">Museo Civico di Catania\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">585\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>A white marble plaque, intact on all sides. Roughly finished on the rear, with the edges roughly cut back for insertion into a wall or other setting. The letters appear to have been crudely repainted since antiquity\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Lunense #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Pentelic\" type=\"stone.marble\" subtype=\"Lunense|Pentelic\" resp=\"#Coccato\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">Very fine-grained, altered, white marble, likely Lunense, Pentelic (identification based on pXRF)\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html\">plaque\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!--Korhonen-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">23\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">28.5\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">3.3\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.complete\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>The text is roughly centred on the stone.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.complete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>V-cut letters of slightly irregular module and height, with pronounced serifs. Interpuncts are above the line and not clearly distinguishable from apices\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line7\">Line 1-7\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"17\" atMost=\"21\">17-21\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270\">Catina\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2525068\">Catania\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.49223, 15.07041\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0151\" notAfter-custom=\"0250\" evidence=\"prosopography\">Second half of 2nd century CE or early 3rd century CE (Korhonen)\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" notAfter=\"1883\">First observed, in the Biscari collection, by Mommsen. Mommsen considered it to be from Rome, but Korhonen rightly argues that the well attested presence of the Pompeii Sosii in Centuripe and Catania, and the physical form of the epitaph make a Catania - or Centuripe - provenance far more likely. Now in the Museo Civico (sala VII.229, mag. sup.)\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">Photographed but not transcribed, Prag 2016-10-14\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"draft\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2019-07-22\" who=\"#AA\">Alex Antoniou Epidoc editing and English translation\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-20\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova added EDCS numbers\u003C/change>\n\t\t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n\t    \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-18\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2025-11-27\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag revised from publication and photograph\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic003150_tiled.tif\" height=\"4912px\" width=\"7360px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic003150.jpg\" height=\"4912px\" width=\"7360px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"rear\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic003150_rear_tiled.tif\" height=\"4912px\" width=\"7360px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic003150_rear.jpg\" height=\"4912px\" width=\"7360px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-14\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n        \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"la\" resp=\"#AA #JP\" source=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>D\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>is\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>m\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>anibus\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>s\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>acrum\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>Q\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>uinto\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan>\u003C/name> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cname>Pompeio\u003C/name> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> Sosio\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>\u003Cname>Cl\u003Chi rend=\"apex\">e\u003C/hi>mentiano\u003C/name>\u003C/persName> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"4\"/>filio \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> et infanti\n                    \u003Clb n=\"5\"/>dulcissimo \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> qui vixit\n                    \u003Clb n=\"6\"/>\u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>mensib\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>us\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cnum value=\"7\">VII\u003C/num> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cexpan>\u003Cabbr>dieb\u003C/abbr>\u003Cex>us\u003C/ex>\u003C/expan> \u003Cg ref=\"#interpunct\">·\u003C/g> \u003Cnum value=\"28\">X\u003Chi rend=\"ligature\">XV\u003C/hi>III\u003C/num>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"7\"/>parentes\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>Text of Prag from photograph\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"4\">\u003Cnote>The F of infanti has a substantial foot, giving the appearance of an E (visual confusion between these letters not uncommon in C2-C3 inscriptions); the A of infanti lacks a cross-bar.\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#AA\">\n                \u003Cp>Sacred to the spirits of the underworld. To Quintus Pompeius Sosius Clementianus, son and sweetest newborn, who lived for 7 months and 28 days, erected by his parents\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>Given that Biscari undertook excavations at Centuripe, and that the family of the Pompeii Sosii has part of its origin in Centuripe, it is at least as possible that the stone comes originally from Centuripe as from Catania. It seems most likely that Clementianus is the son of a freedman of the family.\u003C/p>\n                \u003Cp>Korhonen's suggestion that the apices/interpuncts in line 6 serve to indicate abbreviations cannot stand given that the sign appears after the numeral VII also, so they serve simply to separate all elements on the line, as is typical.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"CIL\">\n                        \u003Cauthor>Huelsen\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1894\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>24510\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/93LFW73G\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000268\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000268\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"CIL\">\n                        \u003Cauthor>Mommsen\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1883\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>\n                            \u003Cref target=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buch/4004\">1088*.282\u003C/ref>\n                        \u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HSQETNGN\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001137\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001137\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"IMusCatania\">\n                         \u003Cauthor>Korhonen\u003C/author>\n                         \u003Cdate>2004\u003C/date> \n                        \u003CcitedRange>13\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/2EUC82DH\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl/>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
